This paper deals with improving the execution latency and energy efficiency of neural networks, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and robotics (cs.AR). The paper specifically focuses on quantization, which is a technique used in machine learning and computer vision to reduce the precision of weights and activations in neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.AR.
